          {
            "commit": "7f40121f5549acb31a07db02d7aa6a8f5817db5f",
            "subject": "LU-8116 build: Cleanup GSS configure script messages"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Quentin Bouget",
          "email": "quentin.bouget.ocre@cea.fr",
          "date": "2016-05-13 07:57:55.000000000",
          "tz": 120
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-06-02 04:45:29.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-8132 tests: do not truncate fsname from paths to ost/mdt",
        "message": "LU-8132 tests: do not truncate fsname from paths to ost/mdt\n\nPreviously the default path for ost/mdt, while defined in cfg/local.sh\nto contain the filesystem name (\"/mnt/<fsname>\"), was truncated\n(to \"/mnt\"). This lead the paths of two different filesystems to\noverlapse.\nThis patch fixes this by keeping the fsname in the path to ost/mdt\n(default path now look like \"/mnt/<fsname>-<component><id>\").\n\nSigned-off-by: Quentin Bouget <quentin.bouget.ocre@cea.fr>\nChange-Id: Icf0baab4a9ceee42116bb12f64c0a07999b10551\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/20188\nTested-by: Jenkins\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Henri Doreau <henri.doreau@cea.fr>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
